HEADWORD: Autoradiography
<hw>Au`to*ra*di*og"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>the
process of producing an <er>autoradiogram</er> by exposing photographic
film to a radioactive substance in close proximity to the
film.</def>⟦br⟧
